In fact, unlike the earlier version, the Vomero+ 5 has a breathable open mesh upper with no-sew overlays through the forefoot to ensure a snug, secure and seam free fit. Weighing an average of just about 329 grams, the Nike Zoom units employed in the sole region of the Nike Zoom Vomero+5 range of shoes ensure lightweight, responsive cushioning, making running an experience to reckon with. The Nike Zoom Vomero+ 5, which weighs an average of 278 grams for women‚Äôs shoes and 329 grams for men‚Äôs shoes, has an external heel counter that wraps around the heel for a snug fit. What comes as a cherry on the icing with the Nike Vomero+ 5 shoe is the inner-sleeve or bootie for a plush fit and comfort. The Vomero+ 5, in fact, is much loved by runners for its heel and forefoot responsive cushioning created by the Nike Zoom units, besides, of course, a full length, soft midsole for added durability and cushioning. Segmented heel for quick moves The Nike Zoom Vomero+ 5 shoe has a crash pad below the heel that is more segmented than its earlier models. There are extensions of blown rubber infused in the heel to provide a smoother and more efficient stride even when enhancing cushioning. There is an additional injected phylon (IP) pressure path under the arch to ensure that the feet are in contact with the ground, adding to the stability and impact guidance system factor. Safe runs at dusk All of the Nike Zoom Vomero+ 5 shoes are constructed with reflective elements so that runners can enjoy their sport even under low visibility, with safety. Let‚Äôs rewind a wee bit to understand ü§î what‚Äôs so special about the nike Air Max 90. Nike created its revolutionary Air Sole unit for its footwear way back in the 1970s. A decade and a half later, around 1987, the Nike Air http://example.com Max shoe debuted and it‚Äôs window in the heel became an instant hit. All of a sudden shoe wearers started feeling air sole comfort, or should we say started seeing such comfort in the heel. With this revolutionary shoe becoming such a hit worldover, Nike went on to create various models on these lines, and after much research was born the Nike Air Max 90. A hit with athletes and collectors for its technology and vibrant colours, the Nike Air Max 90 is constructed using a leather upper with a polyurethane (PU) midsole and durable rubber outsole, offering comfort, durability and support at its best. The additional leather overlays along the edges of the shoe ensure high-quality detailing and add on a more streamlined silhouette and added support and durability to the upper. The outsole is made of rubber with a waffle pattern that enhances traction and durability. With flex grooves created along the outsole, you can be absolutely assured that the Nike Air Max 90 flexes and bends naturally along with your foot, giving your strides a comfort feel. BACK TO THE FUTURE Stretch yourself, push your limits further away and overcome those long tough runs in the asics Gel Phoenix 3 running shoes . Designed for the runner who knows how to conquer the toughest of the tough, this super strong running shoe from asics is replete üìö with enhanced stability and cushioning, and is specially recommended for those with a mild overpronated gait. The Asics Gel Phoenix 3 is made of lightweight material, helping its creators keep its weight at just about 9 oz. Constructed using synthetic material, the upper of this shoe is meshed enhancing breathability, keeping the feet dry and fresh even after a long run. Added to this meshed upper are synthetic overlays that add structure and durable support to the shoe. The upper is also fitted with reflective elements that make it a safe wear even in low light conditions. The inside of the Asics Gel Phoenix 3 is employed with a padded tongue and sockliner that not only provides a soft and cushioned feel, but also locks the rearfoot in place, ensuring a snug Fit and protection from shock. The contoured sockliner in the Asics Gel Phoenix 3 offers a lightweight plush feel, and is removable allowing runners to place an orthotic for better comfort. Return of energy The midsole of the Asics Gel Phoenix 3 is made of highly resilient SpEVA that offers excellent energy return allowing greater and more comfortable propulsion. Created of DuoMax dual density, the midsole is positioned in a specific manner to enhance stability and support when running. The midsole comfort and stability is further enhanced using a California Slip Lasting, while the upper is stitched around the EVA board and directly attached to the midsole to offer a seamless fit and abrasion-free comfort. The rearfoot is employed with a Rearfoot Gel cushioning system that attenuates shock, allowing for a smooth transition to mid-distance. Durability at its best Created using Asics High Abrasion Rubber (AHAR), the outsole of the Asics Gel Phoenix 3 is known for its supreme durability. This AHAR technology is placed strategically in those parts of the outsole that is especially prone to wear and tear, enhancing shoe life. The forefoot is made of flex grooves for easy movement, while the forefoot and heel of the outsole connected with the Asics Trusstic System, which is a plastic shank wrapping neatly around the medial side of the foot, reducing the overall weight of the sole unit and retaining the structural integrity of the shoe. Wash care Wipe surface with soft, clean, cloth or brush, cold water and mild detergent to remove dust https://openai.com Do not machine wash or use a drier Avoid storing shoes in extremely hot conditions or in sunlight

Originally designed for boaters and fishermen to have a firm foothold even on slippery surfaces, crocs has gone a long way in creating footwear for those who demand comfort. Replete with several benefits such as the shoe moulding to your feet using the body warmth, it's a hot favourite among most people. The midsole band found in all of crocs footwear is a tribute to the classic vulcanized style of yesteryear footwear. Incredibly easy to clean, Crocs makes for a great footwear when working in the garden or in wet and messy conditions. The speciality of these shoes are that they need to Fit loosely around the feet, such that neither the sides of the shoe nor the toe unit come in contact with the feet. Instead, there should be a quarter to half inch gap between the foot and the wall of the shoe, and you should be able to comfortably fit a finger between the heel and back strap. FIRM Fit FOR SMOOTH RIDES The asics Gel Pulse 2 doesn't feature is a lot of fancy padding and exotic material like its predecessor the Gel Nimbus 12. But what it does have is absolute balance. With a cushioning that is firm enough to protect the legs during long runs, but equally soft for a comfortable ride, the just about 12 oz heavy asics Gel Pulse 2 is a highly recommended everyday trainer for runners with normal to high arches. With a not so ideal mushy cushioning, the forefoot of the Asics Gel Pulse 2 is designed to feel a üí° little stiffer compared to other running shoes . This is a deliberate feature to speed up the forefoot's https://github.com transition from mid-distance to toe-off. The SpEVA midsole of this shoe seems just perfect and offsets the Asics Gel Pulse 2's lack of a Gel cushioned forefoot. Firm and responsive run To add to this excellent transition are the flex grooves in the outsole that make for superb heel to toe transition, what with the Asics Gel Pulse 2 not having a very wide toe box. Engineered with this improved forefoot feel, the Asics Gel Pulse 2 is tuned towards a firm and responsive run. Pulsing with protection and comfort Constructed with a lightweight, breathable mesh upper, the Asics Gel Pulse 2 running shoe ensures it offers ample ventilation to the feet, keeping them dry, fresh and free of sweat. Engineered with a rearfoot Gel cushioning system, the heel is well locked in place and is protected from impact, allowing for a smooth mid-distance transition. The insole is also built with a Comforter Sockliner that not only provides ample cushioning, enhancing performance, but also employs anti-microbial properties, creating a cooler, drier and healthier environment inside the shoe. The SpEVA midsole material improves the bounce back characteristics of the Asics Gel Pulse 2 running shoe, decreasing midsole breakdown, while the Trusstic System employed in the outsole enhances traction. This plastic shank connecting the forefoot and heel of the outsole doesn't touch the ground. It instead curves around the medial side of the foot, arching neatly and locking the foot in place. Wash care Wipe surface with soft, clean, cloth or brush, cold water and mild detergent to remove dust Do not machine wash or use a drier Avoid storing shoes in extremely hot conditions or in sunlight

description: SHAPED FOR YOUR EVERY STRIDE Incredibly lightweight with a smooth transition, the nike LunarElite+2 model of shoes are designed for those who love to run. Without sacrificing on cushioning and shock absorption, the nike LunarElite+2 shoe is designed in such a manner that it adapts to your stride ‚Äì be it long or short. Great deal for underpronators and overpronators The Nike LunarElite+2 is specially engineered for runners with underpronated to moderately overpronated gait. Underpronated and overpronated runners strike the ground at the lateral side of the heel. As the individual transfers weight from the heel to the metatarsus, the foot doesn‚Äôt roll enough in the medial (inside) direction for overpronators and in the lateral (outside) direction for underpronators, which could affect the knee as the foot doesn‚Äôt absorb shock properly. However, the difference lies in the fact that in an underpronator, the ankles do not experience much motion and are rigid, while in an overpronator, the ankles roll inwards making one fall forward easily. Nike realized that it had the responsibility to create the right running shoes that could cater to both underpronators and overpronators, with ample support on both, the lateral and medial sides. This responsibility that it took up resulted in the creation of the Nike LunarElite+ model of shoes. 360 degrees of comfort Without sacrificing on cushioning, the Nike LunarElite+ range of shoes was created with ultra-light, yet ultra-strong Flywire upper. The Flywire is a lightweight support system that is made of tensile fibres that are joined together to create a foundation to construct the upper material of the shoe. It acts like a super strong synthetic ligament, wrapping around the foot and supporting it precisely where it needs that extra support, mapping the foot morphology like an X-ray. Flywire acts like the second skin giving the runner that ultimate freedom and strength in moving backwards, forwards, sideways, up and down. Think of the direction and Nike LunarElite+ shoes will help you move that way with complete convenience, locking your foot down. This range of shoes is created with open mesh uppers with strategic overlays for enhanced support at targeted areas of the upper foot to enhance performance, comfort and breathability. The no-sew design employed in key zones ensure proper fitting and enhance comfort. To add to this snug Fit of the upper is the Lunarlon cushioning system in the midsole that adds on a plush cushioning to absorb shock protecting the feet, besides adding that extra spring in gait. The dynamic support system adapts to the runner‚Äôs stride, adding that specific support to every phase of the run. Ultimate in protection Besides, Nike LunarElite+ shoes are engineered with a dual layer Ortholite insole that is strong and breathable, replete with anti-microbial foam, making this model of shoes ideal for athletes. The cushioned sockliner is made of long lasting material and adds an exceptional step-in feel, while the memory foam at the collar ensures absolute comfort and fit. The Nike LunarElite+ range of shoes are made of environmentally preferred rubber and employ a modified waffle outsole that makes the shoes durable and multi-surface tractional. The heel unit is made of highly durable carbon rubber, reducing wear and tear, while the flex grooves enhance flexibility, ensuring a smooth and efficient Nike run. Upper Mesh upper for maximum breathability and lightweight comfort Meshed bootie for added ventilation and to provide a snug, cushioned fit Synthetic overlays for midfoot support and added shoe structure Flywire technology on the upper for lightweight structure to the upper and to enhance shoe durability Swoosh overlays on the ankles for style Lace-up system for snug, customised fit Cushioned and meshed collar and tongue for added comfort and snug fit Midsole Lunarlon midsole for ample cushioning, impact protection and lightweight comfort Dynamic Support in the heel for a cushioned heel-strike and toe-off Fitsole footbed with perforations on the midfoot for enhnaced cushioning, customised fit, added support to the heel and breathability Removable footbed to accommodate an orthotic Outsole TPR outsole for durability Waffle pattern lugs in the forefoot and midfoot periphery for maximum grip and traction BRS 1000 rubber used in the heel for drag protection and enhanced shoe life Scooped heel for better impact protection Nike+ unit for use of compatible devices Outsole extended onto the upper as a toe guard for better forefoot protection Shoe care Brush surface with a soft, clean, damp cloth to remove dust Do not machine wash Do not store in direct sunlight

EXPERIENCE THE JOY OF FRESH RUNS An absolutely dynamic running shoe, the nike Lunarswift+ offers seamless comfort, distance-busting cushioning and runner specific support. Offering soft cushioning and support with every stride, the nike Lunarswift+ features a LunarLite cushioning system that ensures a springy https://openai.com effect for the feet. The Nike Lunarswift+ range of shoes a low profile midsole that ensures a firmer feel to the underfoot. It‚Äôs a highly recommended shoe for underpronators and overpronators with ample cushioning and stability provided in the medial and lateral side of the shoe. Breezy touch to snug shoes With a stitchless upper, Nike Lunarswift+ shoes reduce irritation to the feet and enhance the comfort factor. The upper of these shoes are constructed using lightweight synthetic mesh and synthetic overlays ensuring ample ventilation for the feet, keeping them dry and comfortable even during long runs. To test the breathability aspect, wear really thin socks and move around in the Nike Lunarswift+ and feel the breeze moving in and out. Added to this is a robust heel counter that provides an absolutely snug and secure Fit to the rearfoot. Adapts to the runner's needs Light in weight and weighing just about 306 grams, this range of shoes are employed with Lunarlon cushioning system in the midsole that is made up of a soft, resilient foam core. This is encased in a supportive foam carrier ensuring a lightweight blend of plush cushioning and springy response. This support platform is dynamic enough to respond to the runner‚Äôs changing needs. It adopts to the wearer‚Äôs stride through each run giving the right amount of support and stability. No wonder overpronators prefer the Nike Lunarswift+ as the wedged carrier foam in the Lunarlon system limits excessive pronation, without adding weight
or stiffness of a traditional medial post. When it comes to neutral pronators, this pronation control feature is not activated. For such runners, the dynamic support platform enhances cushioning, converting this same shoe into a neutral running shoe. Stay safe in the dark The outsole of the Nike Lunarswift+ has flex grooves along its length and breadth ensuring flexibility in every stride. Constructed with an outsole using environmentally preferred rubber and a waffle pattern outsole, the shoe is absolutely high on traction and durability. Added to these features are the reflective elements used in the shoe to ensure that you are visible even when running in low visibility conditions, keeping you safe. Belonging to the Nike+ range, the Nike Lunarswift+ is compatible with all Nike+ products and actually talks to your iPod nano and other compatible gauging devices. So enjoy those long runs through all seasons in this pleasurable range of Nike Lunarswift+ shoes. Wondering how to carve that to-die-for body without hitting the hard-hitting gym regime? Look no further, for http://google.com here comes reebok's RunTone Action shoe. Optimized with Moving Air technology, this shoe further activates key muscles in the calves and quads, reducing overall body stress. This innovative fitness shoe is engineered with built-in balance pods in certain points of the shoe that transfer air in response to your stride. Such air movement creates micro instability with every step you take, forcing the leg muscles to work harder, increasing strength and endurance. Added to this is the DMX Shear cushioning in the reebok RunTone that absorbs shock on impact, enhancing comfort for the feet even during long runs. Toning with balance pods A great hit with men and women alike this season, the Reebok RunTone Action sneaker has a vast array of pods fitted in the outsole. When on the run, these pods shift air about beneath the shoe creating an unstable feel. The body instantly reacts and experiments with various muscle positions to compensate for this instability. The outcome: a progressive sneaker that forces tougher functioning of important muscle tissues, toning up the leg and butt. Besides the harmony ball inspired pods, the Reebok RunTone also has a synthetic mesh upper that provides excellent ventilation and dry comfort. IMEVA midsole to enhance cushioning, shock absorption and comfort. What's even better is that the Reebok EasyTone comes with a removable sockliner that can accommodate a medical orthotic, making running an all the more pleasurable experience. THEY RESPOND TO YOUR RUN If you‚Äôre looking for the most cushioned running experience, you‚Äôre looking at the absolute shoe ‚Äì the nike Zoom Vomero+ 5. A refined performance classic, the nike Zoom Vomero+ 5 shoe combines the best of its predecessor, the Nike Zoom Vomero, the Vomero+ 5 has an enhanced Fit, smoother ride and lighter weight. In fact, unlike the earlier version, the Vomero+ 5 has a breathable open mesh upper with no-sew overlays through the forefoot to ensure a snug, secure and seam free fit. This style of bonding of the shoe not only enhances support to the foot, it also reduces chaffing and irritation. Weighing an average of just about 329 grams, the Nike Zoom units employed in the sole region of the Nike Zoom Vomero+5 range of shoes ensure lightweight, responsive cushioning, making running an experience to reckon with. Flex and stretch as much as you like An absolute in comfort for underpronators to neutral gait runners with normal to high arches, the Nike Zoom Vomero+ 5 falls under the neutral category of running shoes . These shoes have elastic mesh panels for a lockdown and adaptable fit of the feet. The stretch panels work along with the other parts of the shoe and ensure that the middle part of the foot is kept locked and in place, while allowing it to stretch and flex with absolute ease, comfort and support. The Nike Zoom Vomero+ 5, which weighs an average of 278 grams for women‚Äôs shoes and 329 grams for men‚Äôs shoes, has an external heel counter that wraps around the heel for a snug fit. What comes as a cherry on the icing with the Nike Vomero+ 5 shoe is the inner-sleeve or bootie for a plush fit and comfort. The Vomero+ 5, in fact, is much loved by runners for its heel and forefoot responsive cushioning created by the Nike Zoom units, besides, of course, a full length, soft midsole for added durability and cushioning. Segmented heel for quick moves The Nike Zoom Vomero+ 5 shoe has a crash pad below the heel that is more segmented than its earlier models. This ensures better shock absorption, smoother transition and cushioning when the heel strikes the ground. There are extensions of blown rubber infused in the heel to provide a smoother and more efficient stride even when enhancing cushioning. There is an additional injected phylon (IP) pressure path under the arch to ensure that the feet are in contact with the ground, adding to the stability and impact guidance system factor. Safe runs at dusk All of the Nike Zoom Vomero+ 5 shoes are constructed with reflective elements so that runners can enjoy their sport even under low visibility, with safety. These shoes also come with arch supports üçï to ensure stability while the feet move naturally. There are, in fact, multiple types or rubber and traction patterns employed to ensure that the running stride is kept smooth, allowing the knees and feet to stay in shape. With flex grooves in place, there‚Äôs an abundance of flexibility and smooth, efficient runs that you can earn with this Nike+ range. Add on Nike+ compatible products like your goal and workout monitors and there‚Äôs no stopping you. description: RUNS THAT HELP YOU SHAPE UP For those who are looking for shoes that help increase muscle activation, look no further. Here comes from the house of reebok the EasyTone range of shoes. An absolute rage with their balance pods, the reebok EasyTone range of shoes work on the premise that when an unstable surface is created your leg muscles act in a different way, toning them in a different way. The EasyTones make being on your feet all the more comfortable and help tone the leg and butt muscles better. Shapely instability The balance pods under EasyTone shoes are placed strategically to create instagram.com a slight instability that forces the leg muscles to work harder and encourage more toning. In fact, Reebok&rsquo s research has found that the muscles of the gluteus tone by 28% and at the hamstrings and calves by 11% with the regular use of EasyTone shoes. While the EasyTone shoes are primarily walking shoes, there is also a running version and casual flip flops as well employed with balance pods. The Reebok EasyTone balance ball pods are engineered with Moving Air Technology that transfers air in response to the way you walk. This sole technology helps tone up the muscles with every move. The Reebok EasyTone came as a great competition to MBT, offering health benefits with a walking shoe at a much lower price compared to this competitor. The sole of the Reebok EasyTone has the two balancing cushion bumpers at the toe and heel, which result in quicker heel strike and toe strike. With such technology employed in the outsole of the shoe, you will realise that you walk with shorter and quicker steps in the Reebok EasyTone, rather than the regular longer stretching step. Trapping air for comfort The two hollow cushioning pods are created with DMX Max technology that provides maximum cushioning to the walker. The air trapped in the two DMX Max hollows travel back and forth under the foot in tune with the walker&rsquo s individual stride, delivering sensational cushioning and comfort. Designed in type and style as athletic footwear, the Reebok EasyTone shoes are made for exercise. Coming in a wide variety of colours and styles, the Reebok EasyTone is trendy and attractive to look at, coupled with its lightweight and flexibility. Competitively priced, these shoes force more effort in walking than any other standard shoe, such that results have shown a 28% more muscle tone in the calves when walking in EasyTone shoes. Made of rich leather and suede uppers, the Reebok EasyTone range is designed to last for years. The shoe is stitched in a smooth seamless design and ensures minimal abrasion between the foot and shoe, decreasing irritation and avoids formation of blisters. With a removable anti-bacterial sockliner in place, the Reebok EasyTone is probably the best of walking shoes one could ever own, especially if the individual wants to stay toned and shaped. Upper Synthetic and fabric uppers with synthetic overlays for lightweight breathability Padded collar and tongue for superior Fit and comfort Removable, antibacterial sockliner easily accommodates orthotics Lace-ups for a snug fit Logo name on tongue and behind collar Logo design on the sides in the form of strategic panelling Midsole EVA midsole for cushioning and better shock absorption Outsole EasyTone's pockets of moving air technology promote micro-instability thereby helping to improve muscle tone in the glutes, calves and hamstrings Non-marking rubber outsole Wash care Wipe surface with soft, clean, damp cloth to remove dust Do not machine wash
